cutenews (1.2.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add built-in browser.
  * Add option to set a custom download command.
  * Add option to fetch an article from a URL via UI or 'showArticle' DBus method.
  * Minor UI improvements.

 -- Stuart Howarth <showarth@marxoft.co.uk>  Fri, 06 Oct 2017 20:05:14 +0100

cutenews (1.1.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Mark subscriptions as updated when there are no articles in the feed.

 -- Stuart Howarth <showarth@marxoft.co.uk>  Thu, 04 Oct 2017 05:50:12 +0100

cutenews (1.1.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add support for retrieving full articles from links where plugin is
    available.
  * Add support for portrait mode.
  * Add option to use volume keys to switch between articles.
  * Preserve aspect ratio for subscription icons.
  * Change article delegate appearance in the homescreen widget.
  * Fix missing desktop file for homescreen widget.
  * Fix status changes in article/subscription data models.

 -- Stuart Howarth <showarth@marxoft.co.uk>  Sat, 30 Sep 2017 23:50:28 +0100

cutenews (1.0.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * New plugin API adding support for Qt/C++ and JavaScript plugins.
  * New database schema resulting in loss of existing feeds.
  * Add disk cache for article data.
  * Add user-definable deletion of read articles.
  * Add per-feed update scheduling.
  * Add offline mode.
  * Add custom command and category features to downloads.
  * Add user-definable keyboard shortcuts.
  * Add logging with user-definable verbosity.
  * Bug fixes.

 -- Stuart Howarth <showarth@marxoft.co.uk>  Mon, 06 Mar 2017 01:13:25 +0100

cutenews (0.6.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add support for Hildon Event Feed (install cutenewsevents package to enable and configure).
  * Bug fix: Author sometimes not displayed when viewing an article.
  * Bug fix: Unread articles sometimes set to a negative value.

 -- Stuart Howarth <showarth@marxoft.co.uk>  Sat, 13 Feb 2016 16:04:34 +0100

cutenews (0.5.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add optional automatic scrolling in the homescreen widget.
  * Prevent desktop receiving touch events when displaying homescreen settings dialog.
  * Focus subscription view on startup.
  * Position article view at beginning when switching between articles.
  * Other minor UI tweaks.

